<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-02-09T21:45:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-02-09T21:45:00-05:00" n="434" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d434">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.51/1727: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Eberhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-02-09T21:00:00-05:45"><hi rend="italic">February 9,
                                        1927—9 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received February 10—12:40
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>38. Rene Keilhauer of Hebard Company<note n="35" xml:id="d434fn35">R. W.
                                Hebard and Company, engineers and contractors, of New York, N.
                                Y.</note> who arrived today has consulted me about a loan not to
                            exceed $300,000 which he contemplates offering the Government, half of
                            the proceeds or at least $100,000 to be used to continue street pavement
                            by his [company?]. Loan to be secured by Nicaraguan Government increases
                            reported in my telegram of January 31, 4 p.m.<note n="36" xml:id="d434fn36"><hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_306">p. 306</ref>.</note> Please advise whether the Department sees
                            any objection to this loan.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Eberhardt</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>